    <p>For most of our history, we have put the fate of the world into the hands of a few individuals - kings, dictators, presidents. Some of them have led with great heart and courage, but the conclusion is unambiguous: Our world today is far from its full potential.<br/><br/>
      
      Never before in history have ordinary people - like you and I - had the opportunity to so actively influence the world around us. The Internet has placed access to the majority of human knowledge at our fingertips. It has enabled us to be participants in conversations rather than just spectators. And it has allowed us to form communities with anyone anywhere at any time. <br/><br/>
      
      This is the opportunity to put the fate of the world into our own hands. This planet belongs to seven billion human beings and all of us together should decide what we want our world to look like.</p><br/>

    <div class="panel panel-default">
